# Complexity Comparison

| Approach                           | Time Complexity | Space Complexity |
| ---------------------------------- | --------------- | ---------------- |
| Brute Force                        | O(n³)           | O(1)             |
| Improved Brute Force (Running Sum) | O(n²)           | O(1)             |
| Kadane's Algorithm                 | O(n)            | O(1)             |

---

# Interview One-Liner

**Kadane's Algorithm maintains the best subarray ending at every index and discards any negative running sum, allowing the maximum subarray sum to be found in O(n) time and O(1) space.**
